cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about probabilistic generation of natural language sentences, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes the use of Wasserstein autoencoders (WAE) for this task, which is a machine learning technique, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the second most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the issues associated with training variational autoencoders (VAE), which is a common technique for sequence generation, indicating that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of WAEs for image generation, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and the use of WAEs for sequence generation in general (cs.NE, Neural and Evolutionary Computing), making these two sub-categories also likely.
